# DSN 34-m Beam-Waveguide (BWG) antenna — published reference performance points.
#
# Purpose: sanity-check the UNCALIBRATED physics model (a design-spec paraboloid,
# `dsn_34m_uncalibrated` in calibration_data/antennas.yaml) against real, measured
# deep-space-antenna performance, so we can gauge real-life model accuracy across
# frequency/geometry. Consumed by tests/reference_validation.rs.
#
# IMPORTANT CAVEATS — read before trusting a residual (see conversation 2026-07-10):
#   1. TOPOLOGY MISMATCH. The real DSN 34-m is a dual-shaped Cassegrain beam-waveguide
#      antenna optimized for ~70% aperture efficiency. Our model is a single prime-focus
#      paraboloid with a cos^q feed. A systematic efficiency (gain) offset is EXPECTED,
#      not a bug — quantifying it is the entire point of this exercise.
#   2. ELEVATION ≠ OFF-AXIS ANGLE. `elevation_deg` here is the antenna's MECHANICAL
#      pointing elevation, whose gain dependence comes from gravitational surface sag.
#      It is NOT an off-boresight angle. We compare PEAK (boresight) gain only, so the
#      elevation column is provenance metadata (the elevation at which peak was measured),
#      not a model input.
#   3. PEAK GAIN, FEED ON-AXIS. Measured peak gain is defined with the feed on the optical
#      axis. The harness therefore evaluates the model with the feed at focus (ignoring the
#      design's 0.15 m multi-feed lateral packaging offset, which merely squints the beam),
#      while keeping the design surface RMS so the Ruze surface term still applies.
#
# reference_efficiency is the measured TOTAL aperture efficiency (includes spillover,
# taper, surface/Ruze, etc.). reference_gain_dbi is derived from it as
#   G = eta * (pi * D / lambda)^2   with D = 34.0 m,
# so gain and efficiency stay internally consistent.
#
# Columns (pipe-delimited; '#' lines and blank lines ignored):
#   antenna_id | feed_id | frequency_mhz | elevation_deg | reference_gain_dbi | reference_efficiency | tolerance_db | source
#
# tolerance_db notes:
#   X-band 1.0 dB — after the q_factor fix and P7 auto-refocus (2026-07-10) the model lands
#     +0.17 dB from measured; the residual is the honest prime-focus-vs-shaped-Cassegrain
#     topology gap.
#   Ka-band 1.5 dB — P7 auto-refocus compensates the phase-center defocus (the design's
#     0.008 m = 0.85λ at Ka previously cost ~3.4 dB); the model lands +0.01 dB from
#     measured. Was 5.0 dB while the defocus was unmodeled.
#     See docs/findings-2026-07-10-ka-phase-center-defocus.md (resolved by roadmap P7).
dsn_34m_uncalibrated | x_band  |  8420.0 | 45.0 | 68.0 | 0.70 | 1.0 | DESCANSO Monograph 4 Ch.8 (34-m BWG) / DSN 810-005 Mod.104 — X-band ~70% aperture efficiency near 45 deg elevation
dsn_34m_uncalibrated | ka_band | 32000.0 | 45.5 | 79.3 | 0.66 | 1.5 | DESCANSO Monograph 4 Ch.8 (34-m BWG) — Ka-band peak aperture efficiency ~66% near 45.5 deg elevation
